{"title":"New ultra-clean Trek Émonda ALR gets aero tube profiles, racier geometry and near-invisible welds","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/new-trek-emonda-alr-2023","date":1680784053000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/new-trek-emonda-alr-2023\">New ultra-clean Trek Émonda ALR gets aero tube profiles, racier geometry and near-invisible welds</a></p>\n\n<p>Trek has launched the latest model of its aluminium road bike, the Émonda ALR. Available in two different specs, Trek says the Émonda has been updated to feature a more aggressive geometry, pitching the bike as an all-round affordable racer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In a growing trend away from press-fit bottom brackets, the Émonda features a T47 BB, as well as borrowing cable integration and kamm-tail tube profiling inspired by Trek’s carbon bike range. The Émonda uses Trek’s existing 300 series Alpha Aluminium but, by incorporating Invisible Weld technology, Trek says it has reduced the weight by over 200g on the ALR 5 build.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Trek Émonda ALR 5/6 2023\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Trek</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This third generation of the Émonda ALR uses Trek’s H1.5 geometry, sitting between the pro-level H1 and endurance H2. The ALR 5 costs £2,325 / $2,300 / €2,499 and the ALR is £3,150 / €3,399 (US pricing yet to be confirmed), while the frameset comes in at £1,300 / $1,200 / €1,449.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The launch of the new bike comes with the news that the lower-tier ALR 4 and ALR rim-brake frameset will no longer be offered, meaning the Émonda ALR platform is now disc brake only.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h3><span>Related Posts</span></h3>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/trek-domane-slr-review\">Trek Domane SLR review</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/?post_type=review&amp;p=9748\">Best aluminium road bikes 2023</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-road-bike\">Best road bikes: Best bikes from under £1,000 to over £10,000</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-aero-bikes\">Best aero bikes 2023: Ride faster for less effort</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Racy updates</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-6-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Trek Émonda ALR 5/6 2023\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-6-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-6-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-6-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-6-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-6-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-6-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-6-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Trek</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Trek hopes to capture the more budget-conscious weekend-racer audience with its latest aluminium offering, so one of the biggest updates to the new Émonda ALR is the H1.5 geometry. This fit already can be seen on the likes of the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/trek-madone-review\" target=\"_blank\">Madone SLR</a>. It has a significantly lower stack than the outgoing model – 14mm difference – and a minimally longer reach – 4mm – which Trek says helps put the rider into a racier position.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-5-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Trek Émonda ALR 5/6 2023\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-5-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-5-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-5-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-5-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-5-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-5-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-5-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-5-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-5-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Trek</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to a ‘faster’ geometry, the Émonda ALR now features a kamm-tail aero tubing. Certain tube members, such as the down tube and seat tube use profiles with a truncated rear which attempts to create the low drag of a full aerofoil profile without the associated stiffness and weight penalties. They are said to be inspired by the tube shapes used on the Madone, but Trek has not supplied any figures to quantify how much faster the new Émonda is compared to the previous version.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s also now possible to run the cables fully integrated through the frame, as from the bars they enter the head tube via a profiled upper bearing cover and oversized upper headset bearing. Trek says that the bike is still compatible with mechanical groupsets, though certain front derailleurs will need an aftermarket bottom bracket guide.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Subtle changes</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-4-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Trek Émonda ALR 5/6 2023\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-4-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-4-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-4-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-4-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-4-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-4-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-4-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-4-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-4-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Trek</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>At a claimed 9kg for the ALR 5 and 8.8kg for the ALR 6, Trek says it has made respectable weight savings, making this Émonda its lightest yet.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new frame uses a T47 threaded bottom bracket, a move which Trek has already made with its <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/trek-domane-slr-review\" target=\"_blank\">Domane </a>and Madone models, and one move that is becoming more widespread across the industry. While <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/press-fit-vs-threaded-bb\" target=\"_blank\">some prefer press-fit bottom brackets</a>, issues of movement or creaking have been known to occur, particularly on lower-end bikes where frame tolerances can be less precise.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new frame has no mudguard mounts, which Trek says help the keep the bike race-oriented, and has a tyre clearance of 28mm with room to spare.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Trek Émonda ALR 5 specifications</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023_studio-970x647.png\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023_studio-970x646.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023_studio-300x200.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023_studio-768x512.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023_studio-1536x1024.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023_studio-2048x1365.png 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023_studio-750x500.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023_studio-1140x760.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023_studio-465x310.png 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023_studio-620x413.png 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023_studio-350x233.png 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Price</strong>: £2,325 / $2,300 / €2,499</li><li><strong>Weight</strong>: 9kg</li><li><strong>Frame</strong>: 300 series Alpha Aluminium with Invisible Weld technology, flat mount disc, 142 x 12mm thru axle</li><li><strong>Fork</strong>: Émonda ALR full carbon tapered steerer, flat mount disc, 12 x 100mm thru axle</li><li><strong>Wheels</strong>: Bontrager Paradigm SL tubeless ready rims, Bontrager alloy sealed bearing hubs</li><li><strong>Tyres</strong>: Bontrager R2 Hard-Case Lite 700x25mm</li><li><strong>Cranks</strong>: Shimano 105 R7000, 50/34, 172.5mm</li><li><strong>Chain</strong>: Shimano 105 HG601 11-speed</li><li><strong>Cassette</strong>: Shimano 105 R7000 11-30 11-speed</li><li><strong>Brakes</strong>: Shimano 105 hydraulic flat mount disc</li><li><strong>Bottom bracket</strong>: T47 threaded</li><li><strong>Handlebar</strong>: Bontrager Elite VR-C alloy 31.8mm 42cm width</li><li><strong>Stem</strong>: Bontrager Elite 31.8mm 7-degree 100mm length</li><li><strong>Seatpost</strong>: Bontrager Comp alloy 27.2mm 8mm offset</li><li><strong>Saddle</strong>: Bontrager Verse Comp 145mm</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Trek Émonda ALR 6 specifications</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-970x647.png\" alt=\"Trek Émonda ALR 5/6 2023\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-970x646.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-300x200.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-768x512.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-1536x1024.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-2048x1366.png 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-750x500.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-1140x760.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-465x310.png 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-620x413.png 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/Emonda_ALR_2023-2-350x233.png 350w\" /><figcaption>Trek</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Price</strong>: £3,150 / €3,399 (US pricing yet to be confirmed)</li><li><strong>Weight</strong>: 8.8kg</li><li><strong>Frame</strong>: 300 series Alpha Aluminium with Invisible Weld technology, flat mount disc, 142 x 12mm thru axle</li><li><strong>Fork</strong>: Émonda ALR full carbon tapered steerer, flat mount disc, 12 x 100mm thru axle</li><li><strong>Wheels</strong>: Bontrager Paradigm SL tubeless ready rims, FSA sealed bearing hubs</li><li><strong>Tyres</strong>: Bontrager R2 Hard-Case Lite 700x28mm</li><li><strong>Cranks</strong>: Shimano 105 R7100, 50/34, 172.5mm</li><li><strong>Chain</strong>: Shimano SLX M7100 12-speed</li><li><strong>Cassette</strong>: Shimano 105 R7100, 11-34 12-speed</li><li><strong>Brakes</strong>: Shimano 105 hydraulic flat mount disc</li><li><strong>Bottom bracket</strong>: T47 threaded</li><li><strong>Handlebar</strong>: Bontrager Elite VR-C alloy 31.8mm 42cm width</li><li><strong>Stem</strong>: Bontrager RCS Pro -7 degrees 100mm length</li><li><strong>Seatpost</strong>: Bontrager Comp alloy 27.2mm 8mm offset</li><li><strong>Saddle</strong>: Bontrager Verse Comp 145mm</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Read our guide to the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/best-aluminium-road-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">best aluminium road bikes</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/new-trek-emonda-alr-2023\">New ultra-clean Trek Émonda ALR gets aero tube profiles, racier geometry and near-invisible welds</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Charlotte Head &#124; Tech Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entry